remarks: Strong extensionality of multiplication (expressed in terms of ` <RR ` ). Axiom for real and complex numbers, justified by theorem ~ axpre-mulext (Contributed by Jim Kingdon, 18-Feb-2020.)
statement: ax-pre-mulext $p |- ( ( A e. RR /\ B e. RR /\ C e. RR ) -> ( ( A x. C ) <RR ( B x. C ) -> ( A <RR B \/ B <RR A ) ) ) $.
